      [
      {(A tattered page recording a fairy tale, perhaps accidentally dropped by some child)

Once upon a time there was a young god whose only desire was the love of others. 

“How can I make them love me?”}
      ]

      [
      {“...That isn’t true. The human heart is impermanent, you cannot possibly erase all malice from others, much less everyone who you’ve come to love. Outside of this peachy world, human beings have far more experience and wisdom than you, and the older they are, the more cunning they become.”
So the God steeled his heart and destroyed the older humans - anything beyond his power should be wiped out - and left only the children and teenagers of his age, all of them happily living together, without thoughts of cruelty or malice.

“Now that all are as I am, and I am as all, won't I be able to preserve this love?”}
      ]

[
{I cannot wait any longer, I have to move, to search for the traces he left behind, to find him, I love him so much, I cannot wait here. Maybe waiting is the right thing to do, but I can't do it! Why? Why do all the things I love require waiting? I hate waiting! It's such a cruel thing, waiting! I've endured long nights and cold days, he'll understand my persistence. Maybe my love for him is but ancient history, but I'm sure it will all pay off and I'll find him, even if it's just a broken husk!}
